        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 3.  THE ADJUDICATION AND ITS EFFECT
Art. 2371.  Effect of adjudication
The adjudication transfers to the purchaser all the rights and claims of the judgment debtor as completely as if the judgment debtor had sold the property.</p>
        </content>
